<question id="q1">
    <body>Find the probability for each element in the sample space.</body>
    <short_answer id="A"/>    
    
    <part><response input="A" match="*" score="1"/>
        <hint>To find P(III), you can multiply the probabilities for the three independent events: I, I, and I.</hint>
        <hint>Thus, P(III) = (0.20) (0.20) (0.20).</hint>
        <explanation><p>P(I) = 0.20.  Since C is the complement of I, P(C) = 0.80.</p>
        <p>P(III) = (0.20) (0.20) (0.20) = 0.008</p>
            <p>P(IIC) = (0.20) (0.20) (0.80) = 0.032 </p>
            <p>P(ICI) = (0.20) (0.80) (0.20) = 0.032</p>
            <p>P(ICC) = (0.20) (0.80) (0.80) = 0.128</p>
            <p>P(CII) = (0.80) (0.20) (0.20) = 0.032</p>
            <p>Similarly, P(CIC) = 0.128, P(CCI) = 0.128, and P(CCC) = 0.512.</p>

        </explanation>
